answers.body_markdown:
This is a syntax issue. Your `json` is not [valid][1] because the `json` [syntax][2] want your data to be between curly braces like this:


    {
    	&quot;arr&quot;: [&quot;Hello&quot;, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5],
    	&quot;arr1&quot;: [&quot;Hello&quot;, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 0]
    }

instead of this, which is not a valid `json`:

    {&quot;arr&quot;: [&quot;Hello&quot;, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5]}
    {&quot;arr1&quot;: [&quot;Hello&quot;, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 0]}


Create your data in your map object and let your `json` [library][3] convert (serialize) your object in a valid `json`.


  [1]: https://jsonlint.com/
  [2]: https://www.tutorialspoint.com/json/json_syntax.htm
  [3]: https://www.baeldung.com/java-org-json

